## ğŸŒ€ Problem #2: Duplicate Physics Backgrounds = Disaster

Every menu in my game has:
- Its own UI background
- And a physics-based background with floating squares and triangles (because static menus are boring!)

But when the settings menu spawned globally:
- I could hide the UIâ€¦
- But the physics background refused to stop moving or despawn.

Result?  
**Two entire physics backgrounds existing at once.**  
Floating shapes colliding with other floating shapes.  
Full-on polygon mayhem.

Iâ€™ve seen this nightmare beforeâ€”and escaped it.  
But this time?

### â˜‘ï¸ Fix:
I promoted the physics background to its own global UI too.  
One background to rule them all. ğŸ˜

